description: Fairbanks forms an elite rescue unit called Fairbanks' 11 in order to save Cecania from never-ending detainment by Homeland Security. Some will live, some will die... guess who dies, it's fun! SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

In the aftermath of the Fairbanks' 11 adventure we learn which two characters are long-lost brothers, Cecania and Sawyer join Rondel and Jasmine for a double date of pure weirdness, and Fairbanks and Harmony spend a romantic evening together playing video games in the nude. SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

The gang meets a terminally ill boy determined to spend his final days as Link from "Legend of Zelda". Then to get their minds off the horrors of that reality, they head off to the beach for the now-legendary bikini-clad storyline known only as "Beach Peach"! SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

The beloved "Beach Peach" storyline continues, wherein Rondel hunts for Sea Goblins, Fairbanks is named Hero of the Beach, and Cecania finally bares some skin! Plus, three extra-special full color strips focusing on "World of Warcraft," a sexy superhero Halloween party, and "Star Trek" (with special guest William Shatner, who demands you look at his butt!). SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

An issue full of amazing debuts! A strange new customer makes it clear he "likes to play the video games," Cecania and Fairbanks' long-lost father makes a disturbing return to their family on Thanksgiving, Cecania rings in the new year by wearing a diaper (and not much else), and the Adorable Cyclops Kitten wings his way into your heart for the first and last time! And on the CPP page, look for guest appearances by Paul Rudd, Brian Austin Green (aka B.A.G.), and Zach Braff! (Zach, if you're reading this, we apologize.) SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

One of the web's fastest-growing gaming comics is collected for the first time! Meet the staff of the Sore Thumbs Video Game Shop: Cecania, the busty ultra-liberal with a heart of gold and a brain of silly putty; Fairbanks, her ultra-conservative brother whose secret desire is to play video games in the nude with George W. Bush; Harmony, a ditzy brain surgeon who quit her high-pressure profession to hang out with her best friend Cecania and play games all day; Sawyer, The Iraq War veteran who lost everything in the war but his innocence; and Coleman, a tiny blue polar bear who may be the world's most valuable weapon.

Expect anything in this penultimate issue! Revenge and jealousy, triumph and regret all come to the fore. Fuzz comes up with a way to defeat Victor's nemesis (a bridge) once and for all, but with disastrous consequences. Meanwhile, in the Machiavellian world of the gladiator games, Pluck is king â€” until he finally meets his match.

description: FREE! FREE HALLOWEEN TREAT! Sexy Cecania and her nerdy brother Fairbanks deal with the horror that is the 2012 presidential election. See Mitt Romney and Barack Obama as you've never seen them before!

What happens when the Greek Gods attempt to threaten San Diego with utter annihilation? Well other than outright and total destruction, the everlasting wrath of the National Terrorism Strike Force: San Diego: Sport Utility Vehicle of course! Get ready for nonsensical humor, mythical gods, homages and cultural references aplenty in another adventure for San Diego's premier national anti-terrorist team.

This issue includes Batman #5 & Batman: The Dark Knight #5

Deep beneath Gotham City lies the Court of Owls' deadliest trap â€“ and Batman has fallen right into it! Can he escape, or will he perish in a maze of nightmare? Enter the labyrinth, Batman â€“ if you dare!

When a madman attacks Batman with a new and powerful fear toxin, The Dark Knight visits the coldest and most distant part of his soul. And as his deepest fears resurface, he must rely on old friends to help quell the terrible effects, and to remind him of his true mission as a hero. But what Batman discovers hidden in a moment of courage may change his life forever... for a dark figure from his past has returned â€“ the one adversary The Dark Knight truly fears.

There is a malignancy in Metropolis that is ruining the city, and its name is Superman! The aliens who have been attacking The Man of Steel these past few issues unite to purge the Earth of Superman! The worst part? The people of Metropolis seem to agree with the aliens!

As the assault from an alien threat takes a turn for the worse for Metropolis, keys facts about Superman's past are brought to light for the first time! description:
Collects DEADLY HARVEST #1-4! Core mining, the deadliest job in the galaxy, draws only the bravest, or craziest, workers around. Bumping up to asteroids, typically propelling at astronomical speeds towards distant stars, the miners harvest minerals essential to interstellar travel and commerce. Close quarters, dangerous conditions, and less than a half inch of polymer sheath stand between them and swift oblivion. When the Harvest Moon stumbles upon a goldmine dangerously close to a star, the last thing they expect to find is an ancient alien race preparing to hatch an infestation throughout the system. Armed with mining tools and sour attitudes, Captain Cyrus Layne and his crew must survive the horrors of space and an unfamiliar enemy to escape with their lives. It's Deadliest Catch meets Armageddon and Aliens in a dystopian future.

  • Digital release date: November 7, 2012
  • Print release date: December 12, 2012

description: In rural New England, a hiker is infected with an ancient curse days before his ten-year high school reunion. If his soul is pure he will be able to resist its bloodlust, it not... nothing will be able to stop him! Created by veteran storytellers Shannon Eric Denton (Graveslinger), Keith Giffen (Justice League), and Steve Niles (30 Days of Night), Gutwrencher features dynamic art by Anthony Hightower.

description: When Professor Simon vanished, the Air Force shanghaied the professor's son to Groom Lake to take over the job of babysitting the "problem" residents of Delta Hanger. Now Kirby Simon has to not only process that aliens actually exist, but the fact his father has been running a refugee camp for them under Area 51 without the government's knowledge and the acting up of the "Deltas" has been a cover for the alien's plan to save the professor from his captors. A plan that involves Kirby leading them...whether he's ready or not.

The Summer Fun Issue! Sam Henderson returns with another hilarious Magic Whistle. Dirty Danny, The Brube, 'He Aims To Please' and all your favorites are back, plus a bonus strip drawn by Dean Haspiel. Features an 'alternate' cover by Dyna Moe.

Whosoever be worthy to spend a dollar, this comic can be yours!

description:
Collecting issues #1-8 of the DC COMICS - THE NEW 52 series!

In a new war, the enemy is hard to find - and closer to home than we think! Our only hope is the Blackhawks, an elite fighting force equipped with cutting-edge weapons and vehicles.

Back Blurb

DESTROYERS OF ALL EVIL AND INJUSTICE

Welcome to a world waging a new kind of war, one that's faster and more brutal than ever before. Enemies employ computers, smart weapons and laser-guided missiles to rain hell on the innocent. These villains are hard to find --- and closer to home than we think.

Between us and them stand the Blackhawks, an elite force of military specialists equipped with the latest in cutting-edge hardware and vehicles. Their mission: Take care of threatening new technology before it takes care of us. Lady Blackhawk, The Irishman, Kunoichi, Attile, Wildman, Canada and Lincoln face off with heinous foe Mother Machine while contending with the disastrous effects of public exposure. To top it off, the first clues of vast conspiracy throughout the DC Universe begin to take shape.

The action ratches up for DC's newest team of high-tech military operative in BLACKHAWKS: THE GREAT LEAP FORWARD, collecting issues

#1-8 and featuring the writing talent of MIKE COSTA (G.I. Joe) and artists GRAHAM NOLAN (BATMAN: VENGEANCE OF BANE), CAFU (T.H.U.N.D.E.R. AGENTS) and BIT (BATMAN AND THE OUTSIDERS).
name: Volume 1

description:
When Batman crosses paths with the grim and gritty Judge Dredd, things are bound to get ugly! In these tales from the 1990s, the two crimefighters face The Riddler and The Joker and battle extradimensional gladiators.

Plus: Don't miss Judge Dredd's battle with the Main Man himself - Lobo!

This amazing new hardcover collects BATMAN/JUDGE DREDD: JUDGMENT ON GOTHAM, BATMAN/JUDGE DREDD: VENDETTA IN GOTHAM, BATMAN/JUDGE DREDD: THE ULTIMATE RIDDLE, BATMAN/JUDGE DREDD: DIE LAUGHING #1-2 and LOBO/JUDGE DREDD: PSYCHO BIKERS VS. MUTANTS FROM HELL!

description: Superman and Batman enter Mr. Freeze's hideout, but he's not at home. While Freeze is off wreaking havoc downtown, the Prankster greets the heroes wearing his own giant mech suit. As for Lois and Nightwing, they're trying to fight off a horde of deadly assassins.
